narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A good class to take to broaden your knowledge in the language.

I would recommend this to a student who really wants to learn Spanish. While most students who want an easy distributional requirements flock to Spanish, I feel like that is unwise. This class is not an easy A. But if you want to learn Spanish, you will learn a lot from that.
Good way to learn spanish and overall a good course to take.
A great Spanish course! As long as you have a good professor, the classes go by quickly and you learn a lot in a short period of time.
If you take this course with Profesora Ramos-Ruano, you will enjoy it, very much so.
Highly recommend. Was worried about placing into L2 but it was no problem.
It is a great class that requires a lot of time and dedication.
